{"questionId":"9074591","questionHtml":"<p>A block moving with initial speed <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math></em> is brought to rest, after travelling a distance <em>d</em>, by a&nbsp;frictional force <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math></em> . A second identical block moving with initial speed <em>u</em> is brought to rest in the&nbsp;same distance <em>d</em> by a frictional force <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>. What is <em>u</em>?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074591","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.4","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A block moving with initial speed v is brought to rest, after travelling a distance d, by a frictional force f . A second identical block moving with initial speed u is brought to ","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.1 – Motion","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.2 – Forces","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}